    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Paths\n",
    "AIRBNB_PATH = r\"C:\\Users\\anson\\Downloads\\Assignment\\AB_NYC_2019.csv\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load dataset\n",
    "airbnb = pd.read_csv(AIRBNB_PATH)\n",
    "print(\"Shape:\", airbnb.shape)\n",
    "airbnb.head()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8c9ac428",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "### 1) Missing Data Handling (2 marks)\n",
    "\n",
    "- Identify columns with missing values and decide how to handle them.\n",
    "- Strategy used here (common & reasonable for this dataset):\n",
    "  - `name`, `host_name`: very few missings → drop those rows.\n",
    "  - `last_review`: time field – fill with `\"No Review\"` for missing.\n",
    "  - `reviews_per_month`: missing aligns with no reviews → fill with `0`.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "f4170ce3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "last_review          10052\n",
       "reviews_per_month    10052\n",
       "host_name               21\n",
       "name                    16\n",
       "dtype: int64"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Series([], dtype: int64)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "# Show missing values\n",
    "airbnb_missing = airbnb.isnull().sum().sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "display(airbnb_missing[airbnb_missing > 0])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply chosen strategy\n",
    "airbnb_cleaned = airbnb.dropna(subset=[\"name\", \"host_name\"]).copy()\n",
    "airbnb_cleaned[\"last_review\"] = airbnb_cleaned[\"last_review\"].fillna(\"No Review\")\n",
    "airbnb_cleaned[\"reviews_per_month\"] = airbnb_cleaned[\"reviews_per_month\"].fillna(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Verify no missing left\n",
    "airbnb_cleaned.isnull().sum()[airbnb_cleaned.isnull().sum() > 0]\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fc910341",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "### 2) Outliers Detection and Treatment (2 marks)\n",
    "\n",
    "We inspect **price** and **minimum_nights** via boxplots. Common trimming rules for short-term rentals:\n",
    "- Remove listings with `price > 1000` USD (extreme luxury/typos).\n",
    "- Remove listings with `minimum_nights > 365` (not short-stay).\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "95b3d8e2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Before: (48858, 16) After: (48606, 16) Removed: 252\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12,5))\n",
    "plt.subplot(1,2,1)\n",
    "airbnb_cleaned[\"price\"].plot(kind=\"box\", vert=False)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Boxplot of Price\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.subplot(1,2,2)\n",
    "airbnb_cleaned[\"minimum_nights\"].plot(kind=\"box\", vert=False)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Boxplot of Minimum Nights\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "before = airbnb_cleaned.shape\n",
    "airbnb_no_outliers = airbnb_cleaned[(airbnb_cleaned[\"price\"] <= 1000) & (airbnb_cleaned[\"minimum_nights\"] <= 365)]\n",
    "after = airbnb_no_outliers.shape\n",
    "print(\"Before:\", before, \"After:\", after, \"Removed:\", before[0]-after[0])\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "be924eb9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "### 3) Data Transformation (6 marks)\n",
    "\n",
    "Carry out all required sub-steps:\n",
    "1. Select only **'Private room'** listings in **'Manhattan'** → `data_sub1`  \n",
    "2. Filter `data_sub1` to listings with **minimum_nights ≥ 3** and sort by **price**  \n",
    "3. Create `data_sub2`: each row is a unique combination of `neighbourhood_group` and `room_type` with **average price**  \n",
    "4. Create `high_demand` flag (`availability_365 > 300`), compute `revenue = price * minimum_nights` and display  \n",
    "5. **Bin `price`** into categories: `budget`, `moderate`, `expensive` (you may tune cutoffs)  \n",
    "6. Compute **summary statistics** (mean & median) of `price` by `neighbourhood_group` and `room_type`  \n",
    "7. Group by `neighbourhood_group` to compute average `availability_365`\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "c9a8acf6",
